# Fast Deploy Workflow

- For this project, prefer the fast git-based deploy path over tarball uploads.
- Use `python scripts/deploy.py` from the repo root to deploy.
- The deploy target is the server app checkout at `/opt/endo-bot/app`.
- The remote deploy entrypoint is `/opt/endo-bot/bin/deploy.sh`.
- The remote script should:
  - pull `main` from `https://github.com/Hexttr/endo-bot.git`
  - reinstall with `pip install -e` only when `pyproject.toml` changes or on first bootstrap
  - restart `endo-bot.service`
- After deployment, verify:
  - `systemctl status endo-bot.service --no-pager`
  - recent logs from `/opt/endo-bot/shared/logs/`
- Do not store deploy credentials in tracked files. Keep them in ignored local config such as `deploy.local.json`.
